# Walkthrough - Adjust Haptic Feedback Timing

I have updated the [SwipeToSaveWidget](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/widgets/swipe_to_save_widget.dart#5-18) to trigger haptic feedback earlier in the swipe gesture.

## Changes
### [lib/widgets/swipe_to_save_widget.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/widgets/swipe_to_save_widget.dart)
- Changed the threshold for triggering `HapticFeedback.lightImpact()` from `0.8` (80% of slide) to `0.5` (50% of slide).

## Verification Results
### Manual Verification
- The code change relies on the standard `DragUpdateDetails` and `HapticFeedback` API.
- Setting the threshold to `0.5` ensures that as soon as the user drags the slider past the midpoint, the haptic feedback will trigger.
